(183, 'p8iheZ7g0suqQAqMiYrHLcRevh3Dtz', 40, 1, 2, 5.00, 'a:2:{s:11:\"result_data\";a:27:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:848:\"\r\nCUSTOM SOFTWARE DEVELOPMENT AGREEMENT (FIXED PRICE)\r\n\r\nThis Custom Software Development Agreement (the “Agreement”) is made and effective from 25th Day of January, 2019\r\nBETWEEN:Wizebird Consult &amp;IT Services. (hereinafter  called as the “Customer”), located at 1 Railway Road off Plateau Road Apapa,Lagos Nigeria, and\r\nAND:Individual developer (hereinafter called as the \"Developer\"), a corporation organized and existing with its and operations office at B-11, developers street, Noida, India\r\nRECITALS\r\nWhereas, Customer wishes to get the Mobile Apps and backend of their project for iPhone, iPad, Android (Hereinafter called as the “PROJECT”) developed as per the requirements specifications sent by Mr. Phillip OhwotemuWhereas, the “Developer” desires and offers its services to develop the Project for the Customer.\r\nNOW,\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:1;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:66:\"THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:0;}i:2;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:17:\"herein contained,\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:3;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:60:\"the parties hereto, intending, to be legally bound, agree as\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:0;}i:4;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:3295:\"follows:\r\nSCOPE OF WORK\r\nThe high level scope of work is the development of Project as per the requirements specifications sent by Mr. Phillip Ohwotemu as mentioned above. Creative designs and graphics development is not covered in the scope of work of this contract; however Developer may recommend or create their own designs for the betterment of the App.\r\nESTIMATION AND COMMERCIALS\r\nPlatform iOS, Android\r\nTotal Delivery Time Min – 1 Calendar Months, Max – 2 Calendar Months\r\nQuotation (In USD) $ 2200\r\nNotes:\r\nPayments will be transferred by the customer via Paypal Method in US Dollars Currency.\r\nThe payment is based on milestones, starting with upfront fee at kick off and up to the delivery, divided in 4 instances.\r\nENGAGEMENT PROCESS &amp; MILESTONE BASED PAYMENT TERMS\r\nThe Engagement Process and corresponding payment terms for this Fixed Price Project Agreement are as follows:\r\nAdvance Payment/ Kick off Fee of 10 % of payment – The Customer will pay the 10 % of the total cost of the project as an advance payment at the instance of agreement sign on.\r\nRest of 90 % payments shall be transferred as $ 30 % per completed milestones.\r\nGraphic Design/ UI/ Creative Design/ multimedia – The customer is responsible for, and will supply any graphics/ design/ artwork/ multimedia (sound/ video) required for the project to the developer at either the beginning of the project, or partially during the development. Developer will however put its recommendations; assist in graphic creation for the betterment of the App.\r\nCollaboration, coordination – A status update on the progress of the work will be shared with the customer on milestones basis formally by developer, and informally on weekly/ fortnight/ or as and when required basis. Weekly status calls will also happen to discuss and review the work in progress. \r\nApple’s iTune’s Store Compliance – Developer will make sure that the app is technically compliant to Apple’s App store guidelines, but not the business compliance. Being owner of the project idea, the customer only will be responsible and liable for the product’s business compliance with Apple App Store guidelines.\r\nSimple tabular representation of the Milestone’s definition and payment schedule as per the points mentioned above:\r\nPayment Terms Definition % of the Total Payment Amount (in USD)\r\nKick off feeOn Agreement Sign on 10 % 220\r\n1 Weeks Lapsed App design and Architecture completed.\r\nBackend API partially done.\r\nFront end Apps Alpha release initiated.\r\nSent for test/ review of the customer.\r\nNA 2 Weeks lapsed Backend API fully done.\r\nFront end Apps Alpha release completed.\r\nSent for test/ review of the customer.\r\nPreviously reported bugs fixed.\r\n30 % 660\r\n3 Weeks lapsed Bugs or feedback escaped in Alpha release fixed.\r\nFront end Apps beta release completed.\r\nSent for test/ review of the customer. 30 % 660\r\n4 Weeks lapsed (Final Delivery) All Apps fully completed.\r\nSent for test/ review of the customer.\r\nAll bugs or feedback resolved and incorporated.\r\nSubmission to the stores if all tests are passed. 30 % 660\r\nAfter 4 Weeks Bug Fixing Warranty Time.\r\nIf any bug is reported then it will be resolved on priority.\r\nNA Grand Total 100 % $ 2200\r\nCHANGE ORDERS\r\nDefinition of Change Order: \r\nAny change or modification\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:5;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:2:\"in\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:5;}i:6;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:905:\"functionality or feature or UI of the App required by the customer which is beyond agreed functional requirements considered in this Agreement will be considered as a “Change” in the original specifications, and that shall be intimated to Developer by the customer or vice versa as a “Change Order” in writing. \r\nChange Orders do not however cover any bug or glitch fixing produced out of the code written by Developer as any “bug” will be fixed by Developer for free up to 3 months after final delivery (Bug Fixing Warranty).\r\nSCOPE OF DELIVERABLES\r\nS No. Deliverable Name Given By Scope\r\n1. Functionality Development Developer App functionality to be developed across both platforms, API development.\r\n2.  Functional requirements &amp; UI/ Multimedia, backend access. Customer Customer will supply final design, multimedia, wordpress CMS access.\r\n3. Application package Developer App package\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:7;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:2:\"to\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:4;}i:8;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:975:\"be shared with the customer.\r\n4. iTunes and Google Play upload Developer Apps to be uploaded on their respective stores.\r\n5. Source Code Developer Source Code to be shared with the customer once mutual liabilities are fulfilled.\r\nDEVELOPMENT TECHNOLOGIES &amp; TARGET DEVICES AND OS\r\nThe proposed technologies are as follows:\r\nDevelopment Technologies: iOS SDK, Objective C, Cocoa; Android, JavaSE, PHP\r\nTarget Device and OS:iPhone and iPad running OS versions 5 to 8; Android devices running 3.0 and above.\r\nASSUMPTIONS AND DEPENDENCIES\r\nThe development and unit testing of the products will be done at Developer premises.\r\nThe customer shall be providing Developer with the credentials of its Apple Developer Account’s and Google Play account (required to creating adhoc and final releases).\r\nINTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS AND OWNERSHIP\r\nAll Intellectual Property (including Source Code, Documentation, and Application Package) during the project is owned by the Customer,\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:9;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"and\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:1;}i:10;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:35:\"will be turned over to the Customer\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:11;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:6:\"at the\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:3;}i:12;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:124:\"conclusion of the project by Developer and after the fulfillment of all commercial obligations by the Customer. The customer\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:-1;}i:13;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:2:\"is\";s:9:\"clusterid\";i:2;}i:14;a:2:{s:4:\"text\";s:1479:\"the sole owner of the developed software with full IPR. \r\nTerm of Agreement \r\nThis Agreement commences on the date it is executed and shall continue until full performance by both parties, or until earlier terminated by one party under the terms of this Agreement.\r\n\r\ntERMINATION\r\nThe Customer shall, in the event of Developer committing any breach of any of the terms and conditions of this agreement or for any other reason considered as sufficient, be entitled to terminate this agreement by giving 2 weeks notice in writing and it is applicable only when the project is not completed. If the customer terminates the agreement, then the customer shall compensate